news.title: Mumbai: Nargis Dutt Nagar to give way to residential project, residents claim to be in dark
news.para: While Omkar will handle the rehabilitation of the 1,500-plus slum families and rehouse them free of cost on a portion of the land, its partner, Godrej Properties, will construct the free-sale component as a luxury residential project.

news.title: GST charges will increase home prices by 10%: Credai Pune
news.para: FSI determines the maximum permitted floor area that can be developed on a plot of land and controls construction density in that area.

news.title: Noida: Homebuyers of Jaypee Infratech approaches NCLT over construction delays
news.para: According to the approved resolution plan — passed by NCLAT in May this year — Suraksha was supposed to resume construction of flats within 90 days.

news.title: NCLT approves Raymond's plan to demerge its real estate business
news.para: Raymond Ltd, the demerged company, will transfer its real estate assets and operations to Raymond Realty Limited, the resulting company, effective from April 1, 2025.

news.title: Andhra Pradesh government set to allocate 2,000 more acres of land to Sri City
news.para: Andhra Pradesh govt allocated 8000 acres of land to Sri City near Satyavedu and Varadaiahpalem mandals in Tirupati district at the time of its inception in 2008.

news.title: About 180 illegal structures demolished in Kanpur
news.para: The operation commenced from Bhairav Ghat crossing to KD Palace via Gwaltoli area. According to official communication, four trucks of household possessions belonging to the encroachers were confiscated.

news.title: Allahabad HC orders vigilance probe into Himalayan cooperative housing society fraud
news.para: The court directed the vigilance department to present the investigation report before it on Jan 20, while taking action against the employees of the society and LDA.

news.title: Hubballi-Dharwad civic body to conduct an inspection at Aryabhata Tech Park
news.para: At the ATP, spread over 26 acres, 10 companies were allotted land in two phases for the development of IT-BT industries. The HDMC decided to constitute a house panel to verify the ATP.

news.title: Unfinished housing projects to cost Ahmedabad civic body Rs 46 crore more
news.para: The Housing Improvement and Urban Poor Housing Scheme Committee endorsed two proposals on Friday that will cost the AMC Rs 45.94 crore.

news.title: Nashik civic body mops up Rs 40 crore property tax via amnesty scheme since Oct 1
news.para: In the last three weeks, NMC raked in Rs13 crore via the scheme. The amount Rs 600 crore includes Rs 268 crore as the penalty.

news.title: Dharani forensic audit ordered, Telangana CM flags privacy concerns
news.para: The CM raised concerns that illegal transactions could have taken place on the portal, with some land registrations occurring between 9 pm and 6 am.

news.title: Allahabad HC quashes ECIR and two FIRs filed against M3M India
news.para: M3M India said, "This ruling reaffirms our commitment to ethical business practices and reinforces our trust in the judiciary."

news.title: NCRTC invites bids for leasing of land along Delhi-Meerut RRTS corridor
news.para: The RRTS project is backed by funding from the Asian Development Bank, the New Development Bank and the Asian Infrastructure Investment Bank.

news.title: Himachal Pradesh passes change in land ceiling law
news.para: The Ceiling on Land Holdings (Amendment) Bill, 2024, which enables charitable, religious and spiritual organisations to transfer land up to 30 acres, was passed without any objection by the BJP legislators during voice vote.

news.title: Ahmedabad civic body seals 257 properties of tax defaulters
news.para: ​​Additionally, notices were issued to some defaulters urging them to pay their outstanding taxes promptly.

news.title: Telangana HC directs state govt to release 40 crore in property tax charges to SCB
news.para: The ruling marks a significant win for the cantonment board, bringing the total amount received to nearly 90 crore out of the estimated 100 crore due. Previously, the board had received 48 crore in March.

news.title: Government sanctions Rs 4 crore to Bidhannagar civic body to install 4,500 LED streetlights
news.para: BMC will install 405 LED lights with 90-watt capacity using Rs 1.7 crore and 4,060 LED lights of 45 and 60-watt capacity with Rs 2.1 crore.

news.title: Nashik civic body gets 22,000 new properties under tax net in nine months
news.para: Owners of these properties must pay the tax either from the past two years or the year that construction started for their properties. Hence, the civic body will get an additional Rs 20 crore revenue through these new properties.

news.title: GCCI criticizes hike in minimum land prices for Mormugao
news.para: The GCCI said that govt has increased minimum land rates from 597% to 2,857%, which is exorbitant, unreasonable and unfair.

news.title: Surat civic body revenue from paid FSI hits Rs 829 crore in nine months
news.para: By the end of the financial year, the total amount is likely to cross Rs 1,100 crore, according to SMC officials. The yearly earnings are almost double of the revenue three years ago.
